ZeroClaw architecture plan

Goal
Build a single Rust service that exposes the scan API, runs asynchronous analysis jobs, persists results in Postgres, and serves a React SPA dashboard from the same deployable binary.

Repository layout

.
├── Cargo.toml
├── Cargo.lock
├── crates/
│   ├── server/           # Axum app entrypoint, routing, HTTP state, static SPA serving
│   ├── core/             # Domain models, enums, scoring, validation, shared business logic
│   ├── storage/          # sqlx repositories, migrations bootstrap, persistence DTO mapping
│   ├── worker/           # Browser runner, axe integration, Anthropic integration, job pipeline
│   └── api-types/        # Shared request/response types serialized for backend + frontend
├── migrations/           # sqlx migrations
├── web/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── app/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   ├── features/scans/
│   │   ├── lib/
│   │   └── types/        # Generated/re-exported shared API types if needed
│   ├── public/
│   └── dist/             # Build artifact only, not committed
├── tests/
│   ├── api/
│   └── e2e/
└── README.md

Workspace structure
- `crates/server`: depends on `core`, `storage`, `worker`, and `api-types`. Owns Axum router, app state, config loading, startup, and SPA fallback/static serving.
- `crates/core`: pure domain layer. Defines `Scan`, `Finding`, scan phases/status, severity/category enums, score aggregation, URL validation interfaces, and mapper contracts.
- `crates/storage`: wraps `sqlx::PgPool`, migrations startup, and repositories for scans/findings. Depends on `core` and `api-types` only for mapping boundaries.
- `crates/worker`: orchestrates scan execution phases. Contains browser capture, axe runner, content-safety client, result normalization, and persistence callbacks. Depends on `core`, `storage`, and `api-types`.
- `crates/api-types`: serde-only shared DTOs for `POST /api/scans`, `GET /api/scans/:id`, progress payloads, summary cards, and findings lists. Keep this crate free of Axum/sqlx/browser/client dependencies.
- `web/`: React + Vite + Tailwind + shadcn/ui SPA. Uses a typed API client generated manually from `api-types` contracts or mirrored with a thin TS type layer.

Backend module organization
- `server/src/main.rs`: startup, tracing, config bootstrap.
- `server/src/config.rs`: environment parsing, validated settings, feature flags.
- `server/src/app_state.rs`: shared application state with pool, repositories, and worker dispatcher.
- `server/src/routes/mod.rs`: route registration.
- `server/src/routes/scans.rs`: `POST /api/scans` and `GET /api/scans/:id`.
- `server/src/spa.rs`: serve `web/dist` assets and SPA fallback.
- `core/src/models.rs`: scan and finding aggregates.
- `core/src/enums.rs`: phases, severities, content/accessibility categories.
- `core/src/scoring.rs`: score rules and aggregation.
- `core/src/validation.rs`: URL validation plus SSRF-safe normalization.
- `storage/src/db.rs`: pool and migration runner.
- `storage/src/repositories/scans.rs`: insert/update/read scans and findings.
- `worker/src/pipeline.rs`: phase transitions and orchestration.
- `worker/src/browser.rs`: Chromium wrapper, timeout, page-size/network guards.
- `worker/src/accessibility.rs`: axe-core injection, parsing, mapping.
- `worker/src/content_safety.rs`: Anthropic client, structured parser, mapping.
- `worker/src/aggregation.rs`: combine partial results into persisted summary/output.

Frontend organization
- `web/src/app/router.tsx` or single-page composition if routing is unnecessary.
- `web/src/features/scans/api.ts`: fetch wrapper and scan polling.
- `web/src/features/scans/types.ts`: TS mirrors of shared DTOs.
- `web/src/features/scans/hooks.ts`: submit scan, poll status, derive phase text.
- `web/src/features/scans/components/`: URL form, loading state, error state, score cards, findings lists, recommended actions, re-scan CTA.
- `web/src/components/ui/`: shadcn primitives only where they add value; keep domain presentation inside feature components.

Shared types
- `CreateScanRequest { url: string }`
- `CreateScanResponse { id: Uuid, status: ScanStatus }`
- `GetScanResponse { scan: ScanDto, summary: SummaryDto | null, findings: FindingsDto, error: ScanErrorDto | null }`
- `ScanDto { id, url, status, phase, created_at, updated_at, completed_at }`
- `SummaryDto { overall_score, accessibility_score, safety_score, website_summary }`
- `AccessibilityFindingDto { id, severity, rule_id, title, description, selector, impact, recommendation }`
- `ContentFindingDto { id, severity, category, excerpt, rationale, recommendation }`
- `RecommendedActionDto { priority, title, detail, source }`

Data model direction
- `scans` table: `id`, `url`, `status`, `phase`, `error_message`, `summary_json` optional, timestamps.
- `findings` table: `id`, `scan_id`, `source` (`accessibility` or `content_safety`), `category`, `severity`, `title`, `detail`, `location`, `metadata_json`, timestamps.
- Keep raw provider payloads out of the primary tables unless debugging proves necessary. If needed later, add optional JSON columns or a separate artifacts table rather than coupling MVP reads to provider-specific schemas.

Issue dependency order
- Foundation: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6
- Core domain: #7, #8, #9
- API surface: #10, #11, #12
- Worker capabilities: #13, #14, #15, #16, #17
